RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 69. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR THREE YEAR OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BLUESKIESANDANGELS tracked the top trio in early stages then waited patiently along the rail around the turn, slipped through turning for home, bumped with SPRY CHARLIE at the head of the lane, took command and held firm. COLE SPUR raced off the early pace, launched a wide bid nearing the quarter pole, swung six wide into the lane, shifted in under a drive and finished with good response. GALACTIC EMPIRE settled through early stages then picked up the pace midway around the turn, vied four to five wide for the lead near the quarter pole, swung four to five wide into the lane, sustained bid and secured a share. BRILLIANT COLORS pressed the pace in opening stages and remained forwardly placed up the backstretch, vied for the lead late on the turn, came three wide into the lane and flattened out. ASHWINS ORB raced off the early pace and saved ground, hustled up entering the lane, raced in traffic in upper stretch, shifted out a few paths and lacked a needed rally. SPRY CHARLIE set a pressured pace up the backstretch, challenged for the lead by a slew of runners near the quarter pole, got bumped by the eventual winner entering top stretch then gave way. CALLE DE BOYD got pinched back at the start, moved up into range, dueled for the lead late on the turn then steadied while weakening in upper stretch. THE RIDER OF SPRY CHARLIE CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST BLUESKIESANDANGELS WHICH RESULTED IN NO CHANGE

RACE.FOOTNOTES: LATE FOR LUNCH vied inside of CHEETS for the lead in opening stages, continued to battle for command around the turn, shook free and cleared command in upper stretch and finished going away. ROWDY RAY raced near midpack in early stages, picked up the pace late on the turn, swung four wide into the stretch run, sustained bid down the lane and dug in to capture place. TAP THE BRAKES raced off the early pace, saved ground then hustled up turning for home, roused forward in upper stretch, sustained response and got nipped for place. IOWA CLUB was not too far back in early stages, hustled along two wide into the lane, ran on with interest but lacked the needed surge for serious impact. DREADPIRATEROBERTS raced off the pace in the opening quarter, roused forward to threaten midway around the turn, swung five wide into the lane and flattened out. CHEETS dueled outside of the eventual winner up the backstretch, battled on around the turn then weakened in the lane. MAFIA DON raced in back throughout.
